title: For Sale:  Precision AR15 OPS4 LAR YHM MAGPUL JP Benny Hill comp JARD trigger
postcontent:
AR-15 varmint rifle, 24'' 1/8 ss bull barrel w/ Benny Hill Rolling Thunder comp, JP low profile adjustable gas block, Yankee Hill Machine quadrail free floating handguard, MAGPUL PRS stock, JARD adjustable trigger, LAR OPS-4 upper w/ LAR lower. 

OPS-4 upper w/ LAR ss bolt carrier group and ambidextrous charging handles provides smooth, reliable cycling, the side mounted charging handles providing the perfect platform for scoped ARs, as they do not interfere with optics. The LAR receiver group fits perfectly without play between upper and lower, and it can still be taken down by hand. 

The Benny Hill comp, in combination with the adjustable gas block, eliminates muzzle rise, maintaining sight picture. Adjustable with a small allen wrench, it can be tuned to any load.

The JARD trigger group is adjustable, and it is by far my favorite trigger group on the market. It is smooth and crisp, and this particular model does not interfere with the pistol grip in any way.  

I built this rifle as an experimental project, and it couldn't have yielded better results. I am selling it in order to build a 7.62 version in the same format. It has less than 50 rounds through all new compenents. The rifle has zero recoil, and it maintains sight picture with minimal muzzle rise. It is very similar to shooting an accurized 10/22, though the effective range and report give it away as a 5.56. I do not know what the maximum effective range is because there is not a long enough range in my area to begin to max it out. 300 yards is boring, and, with the correct optics, I think it will easily take out varmints at 600. Feel free to email me any questions you might have. 

The scope is a Millett I canabalized from my old hunting rifle and is optional. I would not recommend this scope for this rifel, but I will gladly include it with the rings for 160, or just the rings for 60.

title: For Trade:  CZ 75 P-07 DUTY 9MM
location: Hammond, IN / Lafayette, IN /, Gary, Indiana
postcontent:
I have a CZ 75 P-07 DUTY (9MM), like new, which has about 200 rounds through it.  This gun has been broken in and tested with Winchester white box FMJ, S&B FMJ, Hornady Critical Defense FTX, and Winchester Ranger +P Bonded HP ammo.  It has performed flawlessly, and it shoots like a dream.  It's been respectfully handled, maintained, and stored for the 6 months or so I've owned it.  It comes with all the accouterments it came with: extra mag, manual, box, etc.

This is a superb gun.  I'd always wanted to spend some time with one after I first saw them come on the market a few years ago, and I've had my chance.  But alas, I'm a Glock 19 guy at the end of the day, and I don't want to spend too much time working with a DA/SA system on a semi-automatic platform (even though I like the grip on this gun better than the Glock), in order to keep my training consistent.  At the same time I'm beginning to spend some time with revolvers, and I'm kind of thinking along the lines of a .357 Magnum S&W with a 3" or 4" barrel for a bedside gun.

Sooooo, the CZ can go, and I'm up for possibly bringing in a used revolver of high quality--thinking along the lines of a Smith & Wesson 686 or 686PLUS with a 3" or 4" barrel.  I hear there are other manufacturers who've made similar guns, but I'm not too familiar with revolver-land.  Basically, if you have a revolver you think may suit my evolving tastes, and you're considering a 'Wonder-Nine', please get in touch.  This gun puts the XDs, Sigmas, etc. to shame with both its styling, fit, and function--it's much more on par with a Glock (I would imagine there are some Jeff Cooper acolytes out there who would smack me for that, squeal 1911, and run off with my CZ while I pull myself together.)

Feel free to throw me a wild card, too, like:

-a Kel-Tec PMR-30, PLR-16, PLR-22, SU-22, SU-16, Sub-2000, or PF-9
-subcompact Glocks of 9mm or .45 caliber
-33 round 9mm Glock magazines
-new Ruger 10/22
-quality used riot shotgun

You never know...

Please be able to share high quality photos of your trade before meeting, and be an Indiana resident willing to give a quick look at driver's license in order to maintain legality of trade.  I'll do the same.

I also have a Kel-Tec P-3AT with lots of extras I'd be willing to throw in to sweeten the deal if things get interesting.

PS: I travel a bit between NW IN and Indianapolis, so I'm open to a pretty wide geographical area.

title: For Trade:  Custom Sako Riihimaki .222 L46 Target Rifle
postcontent:
I have no business owning this beautiful and rare custom Sako L46. 
I'm being modest rating this rifle at 98%. I need to get it in the hands of someone who will give it the care it deserves.
The only time I ever shot this gun, I got excellent groups out of it at 100 yards. I can't remember exactly except they were pretty good for a rank amateur.
After exhaustive research, I believe this gun was built in the mid 50's by 300 Gunsmith Service in Englewood, CO.
The single shot L46 action has a rare solid floorplate. Most singles were pinned. I think this one was referred to as the target model.
It has a Weaver K8F scope, a bedded stock, a split adjustable match trigger, and a 19-1/4 inch heavy barrel.
I might consider taking certain S&W revolvers or 1911 style 45's as partial trade, but otherwise this is a face to face cash sale.
The strange stuff on the trigger and checkering in the picture are artifacts from shrinking the image. Hi res pictures are available on request, or come check it out in person.
